# FlowBoard ShadCN Migration Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Migrate FlowBoard's custom UI primitives (buttons, inputs, modals, badges, progress, checkboxes, selects) to ShadCN UI (canary, Tailwind v4), preserving all behavior, state, and drag-and-drop.

**Architecture:** Install ShadCN canary without `init` (to avoid overwriting `lib/utils.ts`); manually create `components.json` and update `globals.css` with ShadCN CSS variables; install individual components via `npx shadcn@canary add`; replace primitives component by component, keeping DnD structure and Zustand logic intact. `CardModal` and `NewBoardModal` switch from custom Framer Motion overlays to ShadCN `Dialog`.

**Tech Stack:** ShadCN UI (canary), Radix UI, clsx, tailwind-merge, Tailwind v4, Next.js 16, React 19, Zustand, @hello-pangea/dnd, Framer Motion

